public interface KeyedElement
NOTE: This interface defines an element that could be inserted into an internal class called KeyedHashSet. This internal class KeyedHashSet has been deleted. The KeyedElement interface has remained because of the use of it in ClasspathEntry. A keyed element can easily be put into a standard Map implementation by using the keyed element key for the mapping.

An element of an KeyedHashSet. A KeyedElement privides the key which is used to hash the elements in an KeyedHashSet.
